		<b>Comment By Maureen, 8-28-06</b>
		<p>yikes! your first anecdote about the young woman who had her universities mixed up! Reminds me of a bad dream - the kind where you show up for your final exam and forgot to study. Or showed up in the wrong place. Or with only your pjs on. What a bummer for her! Just shows it pays to read the acceptance letter -- at least twice.</p>
		
		<b>Comment By Jessi, 8-29-06</b>
		<p>As always Jenny, great article. How true my friend, how true . I was chatting with a former work colleague the other day about her son (who is starting his first semester at CSU). She told me kids now can order their books online! Gone are the days of starting off school in the enormous line at the bookstore waiting to buy books! My how college has changed!<br />
<br />
And every school year since I have been out of school has just been a reminder to me how far removed I am from that lifestyle now too, so I can relate. On nights when I could rage until 2 am, nights out end around 10 for me now. I have even shaken my fist from time to time too. (those darn youngins'!) Ah, maturity, and responsibility are lovely things eh?!</p>
		
